snippet.textDisplay: "If you're frightened of dying and you're holding on, you'll see devils tearing your life away. But if you've made your peace, then the devils are really angels, freeing you from the Earth." - Eckhart von Hochheim (Jacob's Ladder) Living in fear is not living, it's a slow death. Whether it's 'your time to die' or not (which, whether you think it is or not, has nothing to do with the illusion you can do anything about it) you are already instinctively going to react and behave the way you've been programmed (by your past and society, depending on when and how you grew up) to do the best (or worst) thing you could do for yourself and others. Best thing, stay calm...business as usual as much as possible in your own world, be mindful and unselfish, WE ARE ALL GOING THROUGH THIS NOT JUST YOU AND YOUR FAMILY. Worst thing: over purchase items and hoarding not realizing "hey if I buy the normal amounts of things they'll be there on the shelf next week JUST LIKE NORMAL. :) Life is always changing on this planet (and beyond it) and Always Has (throwing us curveballs from time to time). You can look at past events like the plague and other epidemics, and whether you believe in afterlife or resurrection or not, realize it's all just a game, and will play out regardless of your idea of your own self-importance or selflessness. Eckhart Tolle says 'Life is the dancer, and You are the Dance.' You (we) are in fact, Infinite life. That Can Never Die and Always Continues On (energy doesn't die, it simply changes form, or like The Matrix it's all just a dream). Surely you have at least heard about this with all the "woke" people going around these days, Life is trying to WAKE US UP at this point in our (human) history to show us HOW WE TREAT ONE ANOTHER AND THE PLANET. It's not just that you realize it so you can make a humble and honest decision about "am I doing the right thing, am I contributing to the Greater Good of the planet and life on it?" What about your children and future generations? If you believe so aptly that you are 'only human' are you doing the Humane thing? Crowding animals and people caused this, and hopefully it will help us be mindful to treat nature, animals (whether they be food or not) and Ourselves with the same mindful love, courtesy, and appreciation as we do when we eat that meal. When we see others in the street or work or our families...that we take a second and breathe...and say "Thank You", and consider how we will live moving forward, how we can Trust, live or die, that something Greater is in charge of this Great Game we call Life, so that while you are Here you begin to appreciate this Gift you've been Given (of Awareness, of the potential to be Honest with ourselves and others, of the planet who sustains us and gives us beauty and Life, of others and our interactions, our ability to be humble, compassionate, and selfless) when we stop Needing so much (like children) and let go of that need and anxiety and fear and begin to Trust that "Hey, it's all going to be ok. There's a greater plan than my own that I'm still a part of." This is never the end, and only ever the Beginning. This Moment. Breathe, let go of the need for control (which is just illusory), and Trust...and in your heart "Be Still and Know." ~<3
